In trapezoid $ABCD$ with $\overline{BC} \parallel \overline{AD}$, let $BC = 1000$ and $AD = 2008$. Let $\angle A = 37^\circ$, $\angle D = 53^\circ$, and $M$ and $N$ be the midpoints of $\overline{BC}$ and $\overline{AD}$, respectively. Find the length $MN$. egin{figure}[h]\centering egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (5,0) -- (4,2) -- (1,2) -- cycle;\draw[dashed] (1,2) -- (2.5,4) -- (4,2);\draw[dashed] (2.5,0) -- (2.5,4);
ode at (0,-0.3) {$A$};
ode at (1,2.3) {$B$};
ode at (4,2.3) {$C$};
ode at (5,-0.3) {$D$};
ode at (2.5,4.3) {$E$};
ode at (2.5,2) {$M$};
ode at (2.5,-0.3) {$N$};\draw (0.3,0.2) arc (0:37:0.3);
ode at (0.5,0.5) {$37^\circ$};\draw (4.7,0.2) arc (180:127:0.3);
ode at (4.5,0.5) {$53^\circ$};\draw (2.3,0) -- (2.7,0);
ode at (2.5,-0.3) {$1004$};\draw (1.3,2) -- (1.7,2);
