A wooden model of a square pyramid has a base edge of 12 cm and an altitude of 8 cm. A cut is made parallel to the base of the pyramid that separates it into two pieces: a smaller pyramid and a frustum. Each base edge of the smaller pyramid is 6 cm and its altitude is 4 cm. The task is to find the volume of the frustum in cubic centimeters. egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (2,3) -- cycle;\draw (0,0) -- (2,1.5);\draw (4,0) -- (2,1.5);\draw[dashed] (1,0) -- (3,0) -- (2,1.5) -- cycle;
ode at (2,-0.5) {12 cm};
ode at (4.5,1.5) {8 cm};
ode at (1.5,0.75) {6 cm};
ode at (3.5,0.75) {4 cm};\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}
